2024-02-19.text_en:
Prey to the terrible helplessness that consumes us before a trance that we never wanted to face, Philip's daughters resort to a rosary of baroque farewells, friendly tears and courtly and conventual separations to wipe away the tears that soak our sad eyes. This episode, my friends, is a small review of the sentimental repertoire of baroque farewells: an attempt to search in our most favorite centuries for a little bit of encouragement to give you a surely painful but also very necessary news. But, please, let no one sink into sorrow, as always, at the end of the journey, and of the trip, there is joy and rejoicing, perpetual smiles and Carmelite enthusiasm. We leave, but not without the protection of our angelic squadron of illustrious listeners.

With the wonderful collaboration of some of our favorite listeners:

